&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;About Us&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Red Cell Partners is an incubation firm building and investing in rapidly scalable technology-led companies that are bringing revolutionary advancements to market in three distinct practice areas: healthcare, cyber, and national security. United by a shared sense of duty and deep belief in the power of innovation, Red Cell is developing powerful tools and solutions to address our Nation’s most pressing problems.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;About the Role&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are hiring Forward Deployed Engineers to join a new Stealth National Security incubation within Red Cell. You&#39;ll work directly with federal and national-security customers, and your role will sit at the intersection of software engineering, customer delivery, product development, and mission execution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an FDE, you will embed with customer teams, understand operational workflows, identify high-value use cases, and build production-ready systems that solve real mission problems. You will move quickly from discovery to prototype to deployment, while maintaining the engineering discipline required for secure and regulated environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a highly hands-on engineering role. You should be comfortable writing code, debugging systems, working with messy customer environments, translating vague requirements into concrete technical plans, and communicating clearly with both engineers and non-technical stakeholders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work directly with federal and national-security customers to understand mission workflows, pain points, data environments, and operational constraints.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and deploy AI-enabled applications, agents, integrations, and workflow automation in secure customer environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate customer needs into technical requirements, implementation plans, and product feedback for the core engineering team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own delivery from prototype through production, including architecture, backend services, APIs, integrations, observability, testing, deployment, and customer acceptance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrate with customer systems, data sources, identity providers, and cloud or on-prem infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with product, engineering, security, and customer teams to ensure solutions are secure, reliable, auditable, and operationally useful.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Debug issues in deployed environments and drive fast resolution across application, infrastructure, data, and integration layers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute reusable patterns, platform improvements, and documentation back to the broader engineering organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate with strong judgment in environments involving sensitive data, government stakeholders, and mission-critical workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong software engineering fundamentals and ability to build production-quality systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with backend engineering, distributed systems, APIs, data pipelines, cloud infrastructure, or applied AI/ML systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to operate in ambiguous customer environments and turn unclear requirements into working software.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong technical communication skills with engineers, product teams, executives, and customer stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort working across the full stack when needed, including backend services, frontend interfaces, infrastructure, integrations, and deployment workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High ownership, bias for action, and ability to drive outcomes without waiting for perfect requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
